title: Estrada leads Blue Jays over Royals 7-1 to force ALCS Game 6 (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,439 Estrada leads Blue Jays over Royals 7-1 to force ALCS Game 6 (Yahoo Sports) Marco Estrada came up with a superb start in the most important outing of his career, stopping the Royals' hit parade and helping the Toronto Blue Jays sent the AL Championship Series back to Kansas City. Estrada pitched one-hit ball into the eighth inning, giving Toronto's tattered bullpen a rest, and the Blue Jays beat the Royals 7-1 Wednesday to close to 3-2 in the best-of-seven series. Troy Tulowitzki broke open the game with a three-run double off Kelvin Herrera in the sixth, giving him seven RBIs in the series.
